{
  "texts": [
    "(i) Short-term memory [29] is a limited context buffer for recent observations and dialogue turns, ensuring coherent, up-to-date reasoning.",
    "(ii) Long-term memory [30] is external vector stores or knowledge bases that archive historical experiences, domain facts, and policies, accessed via retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) [31] for informed planning.",
    "(iii) Hybrid memory [32] is a dynamic cache that promotes key short-term fragments into long-term storage and retrieves relevant long-term entries back into the working buffer.",
    "• Interaction.",
    "The interaction module enables IoA agents to communicate and collaborate across human, agentic, and environmental interfaces by fusing multimodal inputs, ranging from natural language and emotional cues to sensor streams such as LiDAR and camera, into unified semantic representations."
  ]
}